{
  "local_port": 56062,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good, low-cost (or free) alternatives to Google Alerts?",
  "response": "Google Alerts is a popular tool for monitoring the web for specific keywords or topics, but there are several low-cost or free alternatives that can help you achieve similar results. Here are some options:\n\n### 1. **Talkwalker Alerts**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Similar to Google Alerts, Talkwalker Alerts allows you to monitor the web for specific keywords or phrases. It provides email notifications and covers a wide range of sources, including news, blogs, and forums.\n\n### 2. **Mention**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with limitations) and paid plans\n   - **Features:** Mention monitors the web, social media, and more for specific keywords. The free plan allows for limited alerts and mentions, making it a good starting point for small-scale monitoring.\n\n### 3. **Feedly**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with premium options)\n   - **Features:** Feedly is an RSS feed aggregator that allows you to follow specific topics, websites, or keywords. While it\u2019s not as automated as Google Alerts, it\u2019s a great way to curate content manually and stay updated on specific interests.\n\n### 4. **Alerty**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Alerty is a simple, no-frills alternative to Google Alerts. It sends email notifications when it finds new content related to your specified keywords. It\u2019s straightforward and easy to use.\n\n### 5. **Bing Alerts**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Bing Alerts is Microsoft\u2019s answer to Google Alerts. It allows you to set up alerts for specific keywords and receive email notifications when new content is found. It\u2019s a solid alternative, especially if you prefer Bing\u2019s search algorithm.\n\n### 6. **Social Mention**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Social Mention is a real-time social media search engine that allows you to track keywords across social platforms, blogs, and news sites. While it\u2019s more focused on social media, it can be a useful tool for monitoring trends and mentions.\n\n### 7. **IFTTT (If This Then That)**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with premium options)\n   - **Features:** IFTTT allows you to create custom applets that trigger actions based on specific conditions. For example, you can set up an applet to send you an email whenever a new article containing a specific keyword is published. IFTTT is highly customizable and can be used to automate various tasks beyond just web monitoring.\n\n### 8. **Netvibes**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with premium options)\n   - **Features:** Netvibes is a dashboard tool that allows you to monitor specific keywords, RSS feeds, and more. It\u2019s a bit more comprehensive than Google Alerts and is ideal for users who want a visual dashboard to track multiple topics.\n\n### 9. **Piprate**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Piprate is a simple web monitoring tool that sends email alerts for specific keywords. It\u2019s a lightweight alternative to Google Alerts with a straightforward interface.\n\n### 10. **Yahoo Alerts**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Yahoo Alerts provides email notifications based on your specified keywords. While it\u2019s not as comprehensive as Google Alerts, it\u2019s a decent alternative for basic web monitoring.\n\n### 11. **RSS Feed Readers (e.g., Inoreader, NewsBlur)**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with premium options)\n   - **Features:** RSS feed readers like Inoreader and NewsBlur allow you to subscribe to specific websites or RSS feeds. You can set up alerts based on keywords within these feeds, making it a good option for curated content monitoring.\n\n### 12. **Zoho Alerts**\n   - **Cost:** Free (with premium options)\n   - **Features:** Zoho Alerts offers a simple way to monitor web content for specific keywords. It provides email notifications and supports various content types, including news, blogs, and social media.\n\n### 13. **TrackReddit**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** If you\u2019re specifically interested in monitoring Reddit, TrackReddit is a free tool that allows you to set up alerts for specific keywords or topics within Reddit threads.\n\n### 14. **Kurrently**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** Kurrently is a real-time search engine that monitors social media and news for specific keywords. It\u2019s particularly useful for tracking trending topics and social media mentions.\n\n### 15. **BoardReader**\n   - **Cost:** Free\n   - **Features:** BoardReader specializes in searching forums and discussion boards. It\u2019s a great alternative if you\u2019re looking to monitor conversations within specific communities or niche forums.\n\nThese alternatives offer a range of features and capabilities, so you can choose the one that best fits your needs. Whether you\u2019re looking to monitor news, social media, or specific websites, there\u2019s likely a tool that can help you stay informed without breaking the bank.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
